10 (4) Each board shall list the current members of the board of
11 education of such school district and an email address for each such
12 board member on the website of the school district. Each school district
13 shall send the list of current members and the members' email addresses to
14 the state department of education and shall update such information each
15 time a new board member takes office or when any change to such
16 information occurs. The state department of education shall maintain a
17 public database of all current members of the boards of education of all
18 school districts and such board members' email addresses. The state
19 department of education shall post such database on the department's
20 website.
21 (5) Any member of a board may:
22 (A) Add {one} discussion items under the category of new business at
23 {item to the agenda of} any school board meeting; and
24 (B) ask questions or otherwise engage in discussion with any member
25 of the public addressing the board at a school board meeting.
26 (6) Each regularly scheduled meeting held by a board of education
27 of a school district, including any meeting that is held virtually or for the
28 purpose of a budget hearing or revenue neutral rate hearing, shall
29 include time for a public comment portion of the meeting. Members of the
30 public may address the board at such regular school board meetings.
31 (b) Except as otherwise provided by law, the board shall have and
32 may exercise the same powers and authorities as were immediately prior to
33 this act conferred uniformly upon boards of education in cities of the first
34 class, and, in addition thereto, the powers and authority expressly
35 conferred by law.
36 (c) The board shall have authority to prescribe courses of study for
37 each year of the school program and to adopt rules and regulations for
38 teaching in the school district and general government thereof, and to
39 approve and adopt suitable textbooks and study material for use therein
40 subject to the plans, methods, rules and regulations of the state board of
41 education.
42 (d) The board may provide legal counsel at district expense to any
43 members of the board of education, or school district officers or employees

